  <description type="morphology">Subshrubs, 20–70 cm. Stems glabrous or minutely hispidulous. Leaves: basal absent at flowering; cauline blades 1-nerved, filiform to linear, 0.5–1(–1.3) mm wide, reduced distally, often reduced in arrays to tiny, curved bracts. Heads borne singly or (sometimes subsessile and in clusters of 2–3) in loose arrays. Involucres turbinate to cylindric-turbinate (longer than diams.), 2.5–4 mm diam. Phyllary apices flat. Ray florets 4–13; corollas yellow, 2.5–7 mm. Disc florets (4–)6–13. Cypselae 2–2.8 mm, faces densely strigoso-sericeous; pappi of 1–2 series of lanceolate to oblanceolate scales 1.5–2.2 mm. 2n = 16, 24.</description>
